The paper proposes a distributed adaptive algorithm for node-specific parameter estimation in a network, which involves the use of Least Mean Squares (LMS) algorithms. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the estimation of both local and global parameters, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of diffusion-based implementation and the focus on adaptive networks could also indicate a potential fit for the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
